            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>My name is Stephanie Ulatowski, and I am currently a student at UC Berkeley studying Philosophy. I hold seven Associate of Arts and Associate of Science degrees. For the past three years, I have worked as a Registered Medications Technician at an assisted living community, where I have been dedicated to supporting the community and residents' families. My passion for law, specifically in the health sector, drives me towards a career in health law. In January 2024, I had the profound experience of donating my liver to my mother, who had been struggling with liver failure. This experience has further solidified my commitment to making a positive impact through law and healthcare.</p>
